<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-25T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-25T11:00:00-05:00" n="256" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d256">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1952</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-25T17:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 25, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 6.12 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2205. Your 1569, September 24, 3 p.m. No knowledge I have or can
                                obtain at present leads me to believe that the British Government is
                                preparing to consider favorably such a proposition but I shall keep
                                the matter in mind and report anything that appears to indicate a
                                tendency in this direction.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>